-- H&M November same-store sales fall 4 percent
-- 
-- Mon Dec 15, 2008 2:17am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/12/15/us-hm-idUSTRE4BE12Q20081215

 

 STOCKHOLM  (Reuters) - Fashion retailer Hennes & Mauritz ( HMb.ST ) on Monday posted a 4 percent year-on-year fall in sales at established stores in November. 

 The mean forecast in a Reuters poll of 11 analysts had been for a 2.1 percent decline, with predictions ranging from a fall of 5 percent to flat sales on the year. H&M only gives round numbers for sales and does not give currency figures. Total sales for the month were up 7 percent from a year earlier, against a forecast of a 9.2 percent increase.